modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and validating command-line arguments, including handling flags, options, and positional parameters. Operates on strings, lists, and custom argument structures. Used to extract and verify user input in CLI tools, such as parsing --version or --help flags and ensuring required arguments are present.

Checks validity of Open Location Code strings and determines if they are full or short codes. Encodes geographic coordinates into codes of specified lengths and decodes codes into coordinate areas. Shortens codes based on proximity to a given location and recovers the nearest full code from a short code and coordinates. Works with strings representing codes and floating-point latitude and longitude values.
